  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Events Manager",
  "description": "<p>Seafood by the River is looking for a motivated and enthusiastic <strong>Events Manager </strong>to support the planning and execution of events that enhance our dining experience and brand presence. This role is suitable for fresh graduates or candidates with up to 2 years of experience who are keen to build a career in events management within the F&B and hospitality industry. Training and guidance will be provided.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p><ul><li>Plan, coordinate, and execute events such as corporate functions, private dining, brand collaborations, and festive promotions</li><li>Liaise with clients, partners, suppliers, and internal teams</li><li>Coordinate event marketing and promotional activities with relevant teams</li><li>Oversee on-site event operations, setup, and teardown</li><li>Resolve operational issues promptly during events</li><li>Conduct post-event evaluations and reporting</li><li>Ensure compliance with safety, hygiene, and regulatory standards<br /></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Hospitality & Tourism Management, Marketing, or related fields</li><li>Minimum 0-2 years of relevant experience, preferably in F&B or hospitality events</li><li>Strong interest in events planning and hospitality industry</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal abilities</li><li>Ability to work under pressure and meet deadlines</li><li>Willingness to learn and take initiative</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office and basic event management tools</li><li>Able to work evenings, weekends, and public holidays when required</li></ul></p></p>",
